title: Second stage public consultation on healthcare reform to end soon
content_text:
p>
    Members of the public are encouraged to forward their views and comments on 
    the second stage public consultation on healthcare reform before the 
    consultation ends tomorrow (January 7).  The Food and Health Bureau released the consultation document entitled "My 
    Health My Choice" on October 6 last year, under which a 
    government-regulated, voluntary Health Protection Scheme, aimed at enhancing 
    the long-term sustainability of the healthcare system, is proposed for pubic 
    consultation.  "Public participation in the consultation exercise is of vital importance.

consultation.  "Public participation in the consultation exercise is of vital importance. 
    Their feedback helps us map out the best way forward. We urge members of the 
    public to send in their views before the closing date of the public 
    consultation by post, email or fax. After collecting public views, we will 
    analyse them and release the consultation outcome in due course," a 
    spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau said. Comments and views can be sent to the Food and Health Bureau by mail to

19/F, Murray Building, Garden Road, Central; by facsimile to 2102 2525; or by email to mychoice@fhb.gov.hk. Copies of the consultation document "My Health My Choice" and related information can be downloaded from the Healthcare Reform Second Stage Public Consultation website (www.MyHealthMyChoice.gov.hk)

and are available for collection at district offices, public hospitals and 
    clinics.
